  "content": {
    "title": "Exponential Decay",
    "definition": "A process in which a quantity decreases at a rate proportional to its current value, modeled by N(t) = N₀e^(−λt).",
    "summary": "Exponential decay describes any system where the rate of loss is proportional to what remains. It appears across mathematics, physics, chemistry, biology, and medicine under different names but identical underlying mathematics."
  },
